<paragraph blockId="4.[151,688,1559,1618]" box="[151,661,1559,1585]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,661,1559,1585]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="4" pageNumber="347" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,661,1559,1585]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
Key to species of 
<taxonomicName box="[365,508,1559,1585]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[365,508,1559,1585]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">Pygoluciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using males
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,688,1559,1618]" box="[151,688,1593,1618]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">Modified and expanded from Ballantyne (2008)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="348" pageId="4" pageNumber="347" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1665,2009]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
1. Median posterior margin of 
<date box="[494,523,1665,1686]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">V7</date>
and T8 prolonged and often curving, 
<date box="[886,915,1665,1686]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">V7</date>
dorsally and T8 ventrally and partially engulfing each other............................................................................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1665,2009]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
- Median posterior margin of 
<date box="[496,525,1724,1745]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">V7</date>
and T8 not prolonged; if 
<date box="[773,802,1724,1745]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">V7</date>
prolonged then not curving strongly dorsally and not engulfed by T8; posterior margin of T 
<date box="[470,528,1753,1774]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">8 may</date>
be slightly downturned but not narrowed........................................ 7
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1665,2009]" box="[151,1436,1783,1804]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1783,1804]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
2. All tibiae curved; lateral margins of elytra tapering posteriorly (
<bibRefCitation box="[834,1179,1783,1804]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347" refId="ref8493" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. (2006) A phylogenetic reassessment of the rare S. E. Asian firefly genus Pygoluciola Wittmer (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae). Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 54 (1), 21 - 48." type="journal article">Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin, 2006, fig. 6</bibRefCitation>
)................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1665,2009]" box="[151,1435,1812,1833]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,1812,1833]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">- No tibiae curved; lateral margins of elytra usually sub-parallel-sided............................................. 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1665,2009]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
3. Apex of median posterior projection of tergite 8 no wider than rest and rounded, not emarginate; lateral margins of pronotum slightly sinuate (
<bibRefCitation box="[383,798,1871,1892]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347" refId="ref8493" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. (2006) A phylogenetic reassessment of the rare S. E. Asian firefly genus Pygoluciola Wittmer (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae). Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 54 (1), 21 - 48." type="journal article">Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin, 2006 figs 1, 19, 21</bibRefCitation>
).................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ballantyne)" authorityName="Ballantyne" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne" baseAuthorityYear="1968" box="[1231,1436,1871,1892]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guigliae">
<emphasis box="[1231,1309,1871,1892]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">guigliae</emphasis>
(Ballantyne)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1665,2009]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
<keyLead pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
- Apex of median posterior projection of tergite 8 wider than rest; median emarginate; lateral margins of pronotum not slightly sinuate (
<bibRefCitation box="[305,684,1929,1950]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347" refId="ref8493" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. (2006) A phylogenetic reassessment of the rare S. E. Asian firefly genus Pygoluciola Wittmer (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae). Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 54 (1), 21 - 48." type="journal article">Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin, 2006 figs 4, 25</bibRefCitation>
)................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Wittmer" authorityName="Wittmer" box="[1283,1436,1929,1950]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stylifer">
<emphasis box="[1283,1350,1929,1950]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">stylifer</emphasis>
Wittmer
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1665,2009]" box="[151,1436,1959,1980]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1959,1980]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
4. Median posterior projection of abdominal 
<date box="[631,667,1959,1980]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">V 7</date>
bifurcate at apex (
<bibRefCitation box="[845,1236,1959,1980]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347" refId="ref8493" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. (2006) A phylogenetic reassessment of the rare S. E. Asian firefly genus Pygoluciola Wittmer (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae). Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 54 (1), 21 - 48." type="journal article">Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin, 2006 figs 18, 26</bibRefCitation>
).............. 5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1665,2009]" box="[151,1435,1988,2009]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,1988,2009]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">
- Median posterior projection of abdominal 
<date box="[631,667,1988,2009]" pageId="4" pageNumber="347">V 7</date>
not bifurcate at apex.............................................. 6
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,642]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
5 Apex of median posterior projection of abdominal 
<date box="[710,746,151,172]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">V 7</date>
deeply emarginate, laterally ensheathing the downturned apex of tergite 8 and projecting laterally beside it (
<bibRefCitation box="[564,846,181,202]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348" refId="ref8493" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. (2006) A phylogenetic reassessment of the rare S. E. Asian firefly genus Pygoluciola Wittmer (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae). Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 54 (1), 21 - 48." type="journal article">Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin, 2006</bibRefCitation>
figs 18, 26; 
<bibRefCitation box="[967,1071,181,202]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348" refId="ref9031" refString="Chey, V. K. (2008) Fireflies of Sepilok. Sepilok Bulletin, 9, 3 ‾ 11." type="journal article">Chey 2008</bibRefCitation>
fig 2)........ 
<emphasis box="[1225,1309,181,202]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">wittmeri</emphasis>
(Ballantyne)
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,642]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
- Apex of median posterior projection of abdominal 
<date box="[711,746,210,231]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">V 7</date>
shallowly emarginate, not laterally ensheathing the downturned apex of tergite 8 and not projecting beside it (
<bibRefCitation box="[583,962,239,260]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348" refId="ref8435" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. (2001) A new firefly, Luciola (Pygoluciola) kinabalua sp. nov. (Coleoptera: Lampyridae), from Malaysia, with observations on a possible copulation clamp. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 49 (2), 363 - 377." type="journal article">Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin, 2001 figs 5, 10</bibRefCitation>
)................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ballantyne)" authorityName="Ballantyne" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[1214,1436,239,260]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kinabalua">
<emphasis box="[1214,1310,239,260]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">kinabalua</emphasis>
(Ballantyne)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,642]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
6 MPP of 
<date box="[303,332,269,290]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">V7</date>
elongate slender, ventral surface shallowly depressed along its length, and bearing on its median dorsal surface two slender teeth; posterior apex of MPP not differentiated; lateral margins of T8 downturned................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Ballantyne" authorityName="Ballantyne" authorityYear="2008" box="[1279,1436,298,319]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satoi">
<emphasis box="[1279,1325,298,319]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">satoi</emphasis>
Ballantyne
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,642]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
- MPP of 
<date box="[309,338,327,348]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">V7</date>
shorter, about as wide as long, ventral surface not shallowly depressed along its length, and not bearing dorsal teeth; posterior apex (face) of MPP differentiated and shallowly depressed; lateral margins T 8 not downturned................................................................................................. 
<emphasis box="[1255,1346,386,407]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">hamulata</emphasis>
(Olivier)
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,642]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
7. MPP of 
<date box="[309,338,415,436]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">V7</date>
defined, longer than wide and either horizontal or inclined slightly upwards along its length and grooved along its ventral surface (Figs 3, 6, 10, 12, 14); T8 much narrower than preceding tergite and apically pointed (
<figureCitation box="[1198,1268,445,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–16" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1912,1935]" captionTargetBox="[208,1361,193,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[208,1361,193,1889]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 10–16. (10 Gombak pinned male ANIC; 11‾16 Gombak pinned male MZUM). 10 terminal abdomen from behind, ventral surface uppermost; 11 dorsal surface V7 (rounded projections of reflexed dorsal margin arrowed); 12 right lateral terminal abdomen; 13 dorsal surface MPP only; 14, 16 whole abdomen ventral (14) and dorsal; 15 T8 with lateral ‘wings’ arrowed. Scale line is 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1457287/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
)............................................ ………………………………………………………………….. 
<taxonomicName authority="Nada" authorityName="Nada &amp; Ballantyne" authorityYear="2018" box="[1212,1353,474,495]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dunguna" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1212,1296,474,495]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">dunguna</emphasis>
Nada
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1359,1436,474,496]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1359,1436,474,496]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,642]" box="[151,1435,503,524]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
<keyLead box="[151,1435,503,524]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
- MPP not defined, posterior margin of 
<date box="[590,619,503,524]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">V7</date>
rounded; T8 not much narrower than preceding tergite and not apically pointed.. 8
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,642]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
8. Australian species; pronotum with wide median black band reaching to anterior and posterior margins; eyes large, subcontiguous ventrally, with well defined posterolateral eye emargination; elytra brown with pale lateral margins.. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Blackburn)" authorityName="Blackburn" baseAuthorityName="Blackburn" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[1236,1435,562,583]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cowleyi">
<emphasis box="[1236,1313,562,583]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">cowleyi</emphasis>
(Blackburn)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,642]" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
<keyLead pageId="5" pageNumber="348">
- Chinese species; pronotum pale whitish cream with restricted median brown spots; eyes not subcontiguous ventrally nor with well defined eye emargination; elytra black............................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Fu et Ballantyne" authorityName="Fu et Ballantyne" box="[1202,1436,621,642]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="qingyu">
<emphasis box="[1202,1270,621,642]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">qingyu</emphasis>
Fu 
<emphasis box="[1308,1325,621,642]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="348">et</emphasis>
Ballantyne
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
